text:
I know this prob won't be read since there'd be a lot of comments, but welcome back and thanks for returning to minecraft...started to feel like I was missing something and realized I needed to watch some Gura streams haha...the early HoloEn interactions (especially the amesame ones, "Who did this, did you do this?" lol) still make me smile like a donkey. Do what you love, Gura, you're awesome as you are. Fauna getting her deserved praise also made me smile ear to ear. Frankly, I know Gura hasn't really committed to anything, but I wish if she does, she'll be able to build at her own convenience; build offline? I'd be ok with that. She's a perfectionist (most people don't really know what that entails), just like a blank sheet of paper's gonna freak an artist out, it's going frustrate her on stream. On stream can be adventures and escapades and leave the creative brainwork to off stream.

For artists, we tend to do tasks that we can auto pilot at the beginning, and then an hour in is when inspiration comes. So how does that translate to minecraft? Desgin a column that you'd like first, and then everytime you begin a minecraft stream or session, start with the easily replicated stuff...after a few you'll get into the groove and will be able to manage the rest of, say, the temple which those columns belong to, or a building here and there. One brick at a time, one short pathway at a time, one small cottage, and eventually after a year, poof, the collection of buildings become Atlantis. Fauna also plans to build her world tree over an extended period, so maybe there will be company every so often.

I avoid saying the end project because that's where the pressure's coming from that's causing indecision/analysis paralysis, and while I'd love to see her build it, I want to see it built on her own terms. Pressuring someone to do art results in art that's not what it can be without. (Game devs under big publishers?) Remind her constantly of the awesome builds she's already done, the secret garden and the haunted house (sure she says it's not done, but having built the outside of that in one stream was already good enough for me.) Hopefully she doesn't destroy the hat house since it's almost solidified itself as a core memory lol. I'd love to see her look over her build like that time she overlooked the EN server and be as proud as we are of her when it's done. It'd truly be a hearfelt moment that I'd love to see.
